# AI Transparency Statement

Everything here is written by me.

Even if I'm pro-AI, when I'm reading an article I would like to believe that the writer took their time to try and understand what they are talking about and respects my time spent reading it. Therefore I try to do the same. 

I've tried to use LLMs before for editing posts, but I found that it made the process boring and the end-result lacking my personality in it. I prefer to preserve my sometimes weird grammar and way of phrasing stuff.

I *do*, however, use LLMs for brainstorming and finding references.
